{
"application": "GSEA",
"software": [
"GSEA2-2.1.0",
"Perl",
"Date"
],
"resources": [
"java",
"xtools.gsea.GseaPreranked",
"/home/michaelt/Data/GSEA/c2.all.v4.0.symbols.gmt",
"${mainDir1}/AllPools.Vs2.QCed.preGATK.QCed.samplesMerged.rmdup.BQSR.calmd.AllPoolsMerged.ChrAll.GATK.RRs.UG.VQSR.SNP.PASSts99_9.wAA.Bi.DropOffTarg_1kb.geno95.hwe1e4.wHM3.justWhite.QCed.DropIBD.EPACTS.${Subset}.${Pheno}.maf1.skat0.perm${perm1}.GSEA.rnk",
"${mainDir1}/GSEA"
],
"requirements": [
"java",
"GSEA2-2.1.0",
"c2.all.v4.0.symbols.gmt gene set library",
"PBS job scheduling system",
"512mb RAM",
"disk space"
],
"notes": "This script runs the GSEA software to perform a preranked gene set enrichment analysis. It uses a predefined gene set library (c2.all.v4.0.symbols.gmt) and a ranked list of genes (provided by the script's input variables). The script runs GSEA with specific parameters, including the number of permutations (nperm) and the minimum set size (set_min). It also uses the PBS job scheduling system for its execution."
}
